{
  "stem": "9665.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my sister Anna, her husband Isaac, Paulette the daughter, and my father and mother, and a cousin called [NON-ENGLISH] left for Perpignan with a sauf-conduit which came from-- which came from Lyon, because we didn't have the contacts in Marseille.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went up and down to get it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Perpignan, they paid $1,000 for an ambulance to go to the Pyrenees.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the passeur waited there for them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made the mistake of paying him half immediately.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He took them up in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jakob ?] [NON-ENGLISH] carried my mother on his back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He also carried Paulette, right, on and off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when they were up there, he took the other half and the passeur disappeared.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The arrangement was that I'm going to wait until I hear when they arrive in Barcelona, or wherever in Spain.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I never had that confirmation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They left in the month of September.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I never-- Leizar, I didn't hear anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I got really worried.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My brother and sister-in-law left a week later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't hear anything from them either, the same way I think.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I didn't check that up with my sister-in-law, because this morning it was too early to ring them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It would have been the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I left on the 6th or 8th of October. 6Th or 8th of October I left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We had a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had transit visas.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was all-- oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I forgot the most important thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got-- was called up to the perfecture Marseille.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I forgot that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was asked, you have got a [NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we had to put that up that we are-- and I said yes, I've got a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And who else has got the [NON-ENGLISH], they knew.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
